text: Shasta Dam (called Kennett Dam before it was made), is a dam on the Sacramento River in California. It was built from 1938 to 1945. It is high and long. It creates a lake called Shasta Lake. It is a popular spot for boating and fishing. ==References== Category:Dams in the United States Category:Buildings and structures in California Category:Shasta County, California
title: Shasta Dam
